DDD 3.1.2 is available					-*- text -*-
======================

Release 3.1.2 of DDD, the Data Display Debugger, is now available at

    ftp://ftp.ips.cs.tu-bs.de/pub/local/softech/ddd/

DDD sources are in `src/'.  Contributed DDD binaries are in `bin/'.
Please try a closer FTP site first; see below for a list.


What's new in DDD?
------------------

DDD 3.1.2 is a maintenance release for DDD 3.1.  It fixes a number of
minor bugs, most of them related to Perl.

DDD 3.1 brings Perl support, Python support, data plotting, Undo/Redo,
advanced data exploration, and several more new features and bug fixes.

For details, see the local NEWS file or the DDD WWW page at

    http://www.cs.tu-bs.de/softech/ddd/


What do I need to build DDD?
----------------------------

To build DDD 3.1.2 from sources, you need:

* The DDD 3.1.2 source package, `ddd-3.1.2.tar.gz'.  MD5 checksum:

	................................  ddd-3.1.2.tar.gz

* Motif.  Typically LessTif (>= 0.87) or OSF/Motif (>= 1.2).
* A C++ compiler.  Typically GCC (>= 2.7.2).

For details, see the local INSTALL file or the DDD WWW page at

    http://www.cs.tu-bs.de/softech/ddd/


Where can I get a DDD binary?
-----------------------------

Self-contained DDD 3.1.2 binaries for several architectures are
available at the DDD FTP sites.

For details, see the `bin/README' file at the DDD FTP sites or
the DDD WWW page at

    http://www.cs.tu-bs.de/softech/ddd/


Getting DDD
-----------

DDD is available from a number of FTP sites:

* ftp://ftp.ips.cs.tu-bs.de/pub/local/softech/ddd/

  Main FTP site; carries DDD sources (src/), patches (patches/),
  diffs (diffs/), snapshots (current/), documentation (doc/), WWW
  pages (www/) and various binaries (bin/).  Usually overloaded.
  Mirrored in several places, including

      ftp://uiarchive.cso.uiuc.edu/pub/packages/ddd/
      ftp://richb-pc.acc.qc.edu/pub/ddd/
      ftp://ftp.th-darmstadt.de/pub/programming/tools/ddd/
      ftp://ftp.gre.ac.uk/pub/tools/debuggers/ddd/
      ftp://ftp.archive.de.uu.net/pub/programming/debuggers/ddd/
      ftp://gd.tuwien.ac.at/softeng/ddd/

* ftp://metalab.unc.edu/pub/Linux/devel/debuggers/ddd/

  FTP server for Linux and contributions (formerly known as sunsite).
  Carries DDD sources and Linux binaries.  Mirrored in several places;
  the file `MIRRORS' contains a list.

* ftp://ftp.x.org/contrib/utilities/

  FTP server for X11 and contributions.  Carries DDD sources.
  Mirrored in several places; server sends a list when overloaded.


Have fun with DDD!

